I have been to this restaurant numerous times before. I live all the way out in Long island and  whenever I come to sunset park I go here to eat food. Well today my experience was horrendous. We waited long time for our food. A party of two go their food before us. I came in with my wife two sons and my sister. We felt uncomfortable from the moment we got there. I had to ask the server numerous times for drinks she gave us the wrong drinks at first second my wifes grilled fish was way 2 salty. They changed it for fried shrimp. Everyone in my family when we got home felt stomach pains and I actually threw up like we got some kind of stomach Virus. I normally never complain but for my whole family to feel like they wanna vomit and my son to take pepto bismol theres an issue here. The service was horrible and the fact we got sick also will make me never want to go there again. I took my Goddaughter for her birthday with my sister and we ate and everything was fine however today was honestly a real off day and a waste of 70 that was spent.

BEWARE OF YOUR CHANGE! I WAS SPECIFICALLY TOLD THAT THEY ROUND UP!  It happened once where I didn't receive my coins. I thought it was a one off occurence and since It was less than a quarter didn't mind.  Next visit, I took a second to notice I didn't receive my coins and addressed it- the response was "OH, WE USUALLY JUST ROUND UP". When receiving my "correct" change I was then shorted a dollar! I told her that she shorted me and finally received my actual change.  IF you'll charge patrons change and expect them to pay it, then the establishment should give out the right tender NO MATTER HOW MUCH IT IS!  Disgusting practice that they have going on.
